com.xith3d.collider
Class BiTreeCollider

java.lang.Object
  com.xith3d.collider.BiTreeCollider
All Implemented Interfaces:
Collider
public class BiTreeCollider
extends Object
implements Collider

BiTree for Collider. This class is designed to be stored and loaded extremely quickly. Because of this the tree is not stored with pointers, but referenced through array indexes. This makes the code more complicated, but it should perform very well and load very fast.

Originally Coded by David Yazel on Dec 9, 2003 at 10:07:33 PM.

intersect

public float intersect(int depth,
                       int node,
                       RaySegment ray,
                       javax.vecmath.Tuple3f intersectPoint)
Checks to see if there is at least one face which intersects with the specfied ray segment. If an intersection is found then the point of intersection is returned and the distance from the beginning of the ray to the triangle is also returned. This does not guarentee that the closest intersecting triangle is returned.
